            "answer_text": "There are Black Turkish citizens who descend from slaves who were freed by Turks over the course of the 18th and 19th century. Their offspring nowadays lives mostly in Turkey\u2019s western Aegean coastline. However, calling them \u2018\u2019Black Turks\u2019\u2019 isn\u2019t correct. Turk is an ethnicity, not just a citizenship (whatever the law concept enforces). And originally Turks are Western Eurasian people in terms of racial origins, so a Turk can have some Black ancestry but there is no such thing as \u2018\u2019Black Turk\u2019\u2019 just as there is no Arab Turk, Chinese Turk, Scandinavian Turk. Our Black citizens are part of our country\u2019s diversity just like we have Kurdish, Circassian, Arab, Georgian, Albanian, Gypsy citizens. ",
